snippet.title: NES Longplay [909] Lost Word of JeNnY: Ushinawareta Message (Fan Translation)
snippet.description:
http://www.longplays.org

Played by: Reinc
Lost Word of Jenny Ushinawareta Message ("Lost Word of Jenny: The Lost Message" ) is 1987 a map-based action video game for the Family Computer. It is based around the Jenny doll which was popular in Japan during that time. Jenny is a 10.5 inch fashion doll produced by Takara since 1982. The doll was originally known as the Takara Barbie, but became "Jenny" in 1986 after Takara ended their licensing agreement with Mattel. -
